post_text: Good evening everyone! Your school librarian here to let everyone know the book fair is next week! Book fair begins Monday December 10th and will run through Friday December 14th. It will be in the boardroom/RM 9, 10am - 4pm. Teachers will plan to bring students down to preview/shop the book fair. Families are welcome to come shop with their students as well. Remember if you come during school hours please sign in at the office. This is a great opportunity to add to your family library, shop for gifts for the holidays and even help fulfill teacher wishlist for their classroom libraries. Happy reading!

post_text: A staff member asked me the other day if our school library takes book donations. Absolutely! We accept gently used children‚Äôs , teen and YA ( young adult) books. Please sign into the main office before coming up to the library to drop off. We would love and appreciate your donations. It keeps a great selection of literature and media circulating through our library for our students to expand their reading.

post_text:
Friends of the Tuolumne County Library will host the Fall Book Sale on Friday, November 2nd and Saturday, November 3rd in the Community Meeting Room at Sonora Main Library located at 480 Greenley Road, Sonora. Purchase gently-used books at bargain prices! All proceeds fund library programs and services.
On Friday, November 2nd from 10:00 - 1:00, it's Members Only. (You may join Friends of the Library at the door.) Members get first choice of books, and there will be refreshments.
On Friday, November 2nd from 1:00 - 4:00, and Saturday, November 3rd from 10:00 - 4:00, the Fall Book Sale is open to the public.
Here are the book prices:
Hardbound Fiction $2.00
Hardbound Thrillers & Non-fiction $1.00
Trade Paperbacks $0.50
Other Paperbacks $0.25

Note: All books in The Book Nook at Sonora Main will be half-price during the Fall Book Sale.
Note: On Saturday, starting at 2:30 p.m., a bag of books will cost $5.00 - you choose the books!

GOT BOOKS? STOCK UP FOR YOUR WINTER READING!

RED RIBBON/CHARACTER COUNTS WEEK will be observed the week of October 29th. Students in TK-
1st grade are asked to show their school spirit and good character by wearing the color of that day‚Äôs trait. Students in the 2nd-8th grade may participate in the dress up theme for the day but all clothing and accessories must conform to our school dress code.

* Monday 10/29=Crazy Everything or wear Red for Caring

* Tuesday 10/30=Tie Dye or wear Blue & Yellow for Trustworthiness & Respect

* Wednesday 10/31=Halloween Costume or wear Orange for Fairness

* Thursday 11/1= Tourist or wear Purple for Citizenship

* Friday 11/2= Meme/Cartoon or wear Green for Spirit & Responsibility
